<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-01-29T23:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-01-29T23:00:00-05:00" n="235" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d235">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 839.51/1213c.</note>
                        <head ana="#head_untitled-inferred-from-preceding-sibling-head">[Untitled]</head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-01-29T23:00:00-05:00">
                                    <hi rend="italic">January 29, 1914, 11 p.m.</hi>
                                </date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>You may inform Minister for Foreign Affairs that Department has consulted
                            President and will send commercial attaché on receipt of written request
                            expressed as required in Department’s telegram of January 27, 8 p.m.
                            Your January 28, 2 p.m., just received, will consider relief measures
                            tomorrow.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Bryan</hi></signed>.</closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>